# MARS API LatAm — Project Overview

## Stack

- **Python 3.10+**, `httpx`, `pydantic-settings`, `streamlit`, `plotly`, `pandas`
- **Linter/formatter**: `ruff` (line length 110, target py311)
- **Auth**: HS256 JWT generated in `bloomberg/webapi/bbg_jwt.py`

## Layer Architecture

```
bloomberg/webapi/mars_client.py   ← low-level HTTP + JWT + session management
services/curves_service.py        ← XMarket curve downloads (supports demo mode)
services/security_service.py      ← deal structure + price + solve + save
services/portfolio_service.py     ← portfolio pricing
services/risk_service.py          ← Key Rate Risk (KRR)
instruments/swap.py               ← Pydantic model → MARS params
instruments/fx_option.py
instruments/equity_option.py
configs/settings.py               ← credentials + constants (pydantic-settings)
configs/i18n.py                   ← UI translations EN/PT/ES
configs/curves_catalog.py         ← 248-entry XMarket curve catalog
pages/1_📈_Curves.py              ← Streamlit UI pages
app.py                            ← Streamlit home page
demo_data/                        ← pre-saved JSON curve snapshots for demo mode
```

## Key Conventions

- **Demo mode**: `settings.demo_mode` is `True` when no Bloomberg credentials are set. Services must handle this gracefully — `CurvesService` loads from `demo_data/`.
- **Credentials**: Never hardcode. Always read from `.env` via `pydantic-settings`. `.env` is gitignored.
- **Structure requests**: Use `"tail"` + `"dealStructureOverride"` body format (NOT `"structureRequest"`).
- **DayCount**: Use MARS notation (`"ACT/365"`, `"ACT/360"`) not long-form.
- **Curve IDs**: Format is `S{number}` (e.g. `S329` for COP OIS).
- **Comments and docstrings**: Always in English.
- **UI strings**: Always via `t(key)` from `configs.i18n` — never hardcoded in page files.
